nodes.bodyText: What is the latest Linux 7.x node image?
Via OCI dashboard it is Oracle-Linux-7.8-2020-09-23-0 but somehow via terraform this value is not accepted so the latest via terraform is Oracle-Linux-7.6 , it is also configurable in jerking job
Can't we have a suitable default for NFS_SERVER and FSS_DIR ?  We need this when OKE_CLUSTER is set to true.
no we can can't , it is created during runtime, since I create MountTarget at the same time as OKE cluster
We have similar method ( createPvAndPvc) with same name in ItMonitoringExporter.java.  Can we merge these two.
I need to fix MonExporter separately, it requires more changes for prometheus and grafana pvs I will do it in different jira
Can we re use the tf files in weblogic-kubernetes-operator/kubernetes/samples/scripts/terraform directory, so that we can verify what we ship with the sample.

there are changes applicable to Jenkins run requirements , for example we use only 2 nodes instead 3, also vcn setup is different, we also have extra *tf files for mount target, exports, and file system
